Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the National Rifle Association's annual meeting in Dallas, Texas. He expressed his support for the Second Amendment and praised President Donald Trump's commitment to protecting gun rights. Pence also discussed the administration's efforts to strengthen border security, enforce laws, and provide resources for law enforcement. He highlighted stories of individuals who used firearms to protect themselves and others, calling for the media to give more attention to these stories. Pence also addressed the issue of mass shootings and outlined the administration's actions to improve school safety and address mental illness. He concluded by urging NRA members to continue defending their rights and supporting conservative leaders.